    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-12T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-12T16:00:00-05:00" n="325"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d325">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4163b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="#p_CES1" type="to"
                            >Cunningham</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-12T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 12, 1932—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>16. For the Minister and Consul-General. For your confidential information and
                    guidance.</p>
                <p>Reference Department’s telegram to the American Consul, Shanghai, No. 13 of
                    February 10, 8 p.m.</p>
                <p>The Department has today telegraphed Minister <persName corresp="#p_WHR1"
                        >Wilson</persName> at Geneva, for discreet communication to <persName
                        corresp="#p_DSE1">Drummond</persName>, in part as follows: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Any effort which any agency may make at this time toward the objective
                            of bringing the hostilities to an end will have my approval in
                            principle”.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
